{{refimprove|date=February 2013}}
{{Politics of Cambodia}}
The '''politics of Cambodia''' takes place in a framework of a [[constitutional monarchy]], whereby the [[Prime Minister of Cambodia|Prime Minister]] is the [[head of government]] and a [[monarchy|Monarch]] is [[head of state]]. The kingdom formally operates according to the nation's [[constitution]] (enacted in 1993) in a framework of a [[parliamentary system|parliamentary]], [[representative democracy]]. [[Executive power]] is exercised by the government. [[Legislative power]] is vested in the two chambers of parliament, the [[National Assembly of Cambodia|National Assembly]] and the [[Senate of Cambodia|Senate]].

==Executive branch==
{{office-table}}
|[[King of Cambodia|King]]
