==Provincial and local governments==
{{see also|Administrative divisions of Cambodia}}
Below the central government are 24 provincial and municipal administration.<ref name=wb>''Private Solutions for Infrastructure in Cambodia: A Country Framework Report''. [[World Bank]] (2002), [http://books.google.com/books?id=ktRy_5sKrGEC&pg=PA65&sig=hu1tsbqolFnZgX3g4mOpv87NarE p65]. ISBN 0-8213-5076-5.</ref> (In rural areas, first-level administrative divisions are called provinces; in urban areas, they are called municipalities.)  The administrations are a part of the [[Ministry of the Interior (Cambodia)|Ministry of the Interior]] and their members are appointed by the central government.<ref name=wb/> Provincial and municipal administrations participate in the creation of nation budget; they also issue land titles and license businesses.<ref name=wb/>  

Since 2002, commune-level governments ([[commune council]]s) have been composed of members directly elected by commune residents every five years.<ref>[http://www.embassyofcambodia.org.nz/March2007/March2007-3.htm Untitled Document<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

In practice, the allocation of responsibilities between various levels of government is uncertain.<ref name=wb/>  This uncertainty has created additional opportunities for corruption and increased costs for investors.<ref name=wb/>

